The core of the distribution area falls within a humid [[foothills|piedmont]] zone with the land consisting of volcanic soil and rubble carried down from the mountains, with naturally occurring basalt boulders of varying sizes that provided a practical raw material for sculpture.<ref>McInnis Thompson & Valdez 2008, p.21.</ref> Potbelly sculptures are found in prominent ceremonial centres.<ref>McInnis Thompson & Valdez 2008, p.24.</ref>

