===Guatemala===
[[Image:Potbelly 1.jpg|thumb|right|Monument 109 at Takalik Abaj, a small potbelly sculpture.<ref>Orrego Corzo & Schieber de Lavarreda 2001, pp.791-2.</ref>]]
Examples have been found at many sites on the Pacific coast of Guatemala including Takalik Abaj, [[Monte Alto culture|Monte Alto]], Bilbao and [[El Ba<U+00FA>l]]. The earliest examples of potbellied monuments have been dated to the Middle Preclassic, with the majority dating to the Late Preclassic.<ref>Sharer 2000, pp.476-477.</ref>

Well-preserved examples of Late Preclassic potbelly sculptures have been found at Bilbao, on the coastal plain, and at Kaminaljuyu in the Guatemalan highlands.<ref>Sharer & Traxler 2006, p.245.</ref> A small potbelly monument has been found at the major Maya city of Tikal in the lowlands of [[Pet<U+00E9>n Basin|Pet<U+00E9>n]] in Guatemala.<ref>Sharer 2000, p.476.</ref>

